The paper focuses on obstacle avoidance for autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper uses deep reinforcement learning with monocular RGB vision, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of reinforcement learning also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of the trained models to real robots, which involves system and control (cs.SY).
